== Potatoes ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a
large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half
the @mustard seeds{1}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

== Crust ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and
@North Indian Style spice mix{1}.

Add the @olive oil{for the crumb} and @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine.

== Salmon ==

Pat the @salmon fillets{2} with #kitchen paper{} to remove any excess moisture,
then lay the fillets, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray.

Spread the @mango chutney{40%g} over the top of the fish and top with the
breadcrumb mixture. Press it down with a #spoon{}, then set aside for now.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

== Zesty Mayo ==

Zest and cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges.

In another small bowl, mix together the @mayonnaise{32%g} with the lime zest.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Green Beans ==

Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

While everything cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and remaining @mustard seeds{}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.
Allow to cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Finishing ==

About 10 mins before the potatoes are cooked, bake the salmon on the middle
shelf of the oven until the crumb is golden and the fish is cooked through,
~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

When everything's ready, plate up your salmon with the potatoes and green
beans alongside.

Serve with a dollop of zesty mayo and the lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!